# Fixture FM4a: Empty collection must resolve to rdf:nil (not a blank node).
#
# Hypothesis: A parser that generates a fresh blank node for `()` is wrong.
# `()` must be exactly <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil>.
#
# Expected triples:
#   <http://example/s> <http://example/p>
#       <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil> .
#
# Divergence signal: FactOnlyIn if one parser emits a bnode instead of
# rdf:nil, because the fact sets will not match on the object.
#
# Spec: Turtle §2.8; `() = rdf:nil`.
# Errata: w3c/rdf-tests issue #115.

<http://example/s> <http://example/p> () .
